LOCUS       SnoopTag                  12 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  SnoopTag: a 12-aa peptide split from the D4 domain of Streptococcus
            pneumoniae RrgA that spontaneously forms a covalent isopeptide bond
            with its partner protein SnoopCatcher (>99% yield) and is orthogonal
            to SpyTag/SpyCatcher..
